      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "INSIDER TRADING (1) added to a string of wins and placings when he recorded an easy win last time out, scoring by more than 9 metres at this venue. Hard to knock the consistency and the inside draw should give him every chance to strike again. ANOTHER WOODS (9) made it two wins from his last four runs when getting home by 3.7 metres at Geelong last week. May be relying on some luck from his back row draw but he has won here before. KING SAINT (4) put the writing on the wall with back-to-back placings before leading to score last start by 1.8 metres at Kilmore. Expect him to be competitive again. IM WESLEY (2) is back from a freshen but he draws well and came from wider barriers to place in his last two outings. YA BOTTOM DOLLAR (5) deserved the last-start win and is proven at this circuit and distance so while drawn wider he can continue the good form.",
